---
---
<section id="projects">
  <h2 class="fade-in">Projects</h2>

  <div class="project fade-in">
    <div class="project-header">
      <h3>AI DevSec Platform</h3>
      <span class="date">2026 - present</span>
    </div>
    <p class="stack">Python, FastAPI, React, Pytest</p>
    <p>
      Static application security testing tool that scans source code and git diffs for 10 vulnerability classes including SQL injection, hardcoded secrets, and path traversal. 42 test cases and color-coded risk scoring frontend.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/Sudhakar-exe/ai-devsec-platform" target="_blank" class="project-link">View on GitHub →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="project fade-in">
    <div class="project-header">
      <h3>AI Health Monitoring System</h3>
      <span class="date">2026</span>
    </div>
    <p class="stack">Raspberry Pi, Arduino, Flask, Chart.js, Claude API</p>
    <p>
      Hardware project with LM35 and MAX30102 sensors streaming live vitals to a Flask dashboard. Persists data in SQLite and uses the Anthropic API for health insights. Built with a team of 3.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="project fade-in">
    <div class="project-header">
      <h3>Task & Time Management App</h3>
      <span class="date">Spring 2025</span>
    </div>
    <p class="stack">C#, .NET, React, TypeScript, OAuth, JWT</p>
    <p>
      Led a 4-member Agile team in our SWE class to build a full-stack task platform with role-based access control and authenticated REST APIs. Managed sprint planning, Git collaboration, and documentation.
    </p>
    <div class="project-photo">
      <img src="/images/swe-team.jpg" alt="SWE class team with professor" loading="lazy" />
      <span class="caption">Our team with our professor</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="project fade-in">
    <div class="project-header">
      <h3>Paobucks - Coffee Ordering App</h3>
      <span class="date">Fall 2025</span>
    </div>
    <p class="stack">Kotlin, Android SDK</p>
    <p>
      Native Android app with dynamic pricing, order state management, and scalable menu rendering. Clean separation of UI and business logic.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="project fade-in">
    <div class="project-header">
      <h3>CTF Competitions</h3>
      <span class="date">2024 - present</span>
    </div>
    <p class="stack">Wireshark, Nmap, TryHackMe, forensics tools</p>
    <p>
      Ongoing work in penetration testing, Windows event log forensics, steganography, and cryptographic challenges across TryHackMe and national competitions.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .project {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .project:last-child { border-bottom: none; margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; }
  .project-header {
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem; gap: 1rem;
  }
  .project-header h3 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .date { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--light); white-space: nowrap; }
  .stack { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--light); margin-bottom: 0.65rem; }
  .project p:not(.stack) { color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.75; }
  .project-link {
    display: inline-block; margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text); text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }
  .project-link:hover { border-color: var(--text); opacity: 1; }
  .project-photo { margin-top: 1.25rem; overflow: hidden; border-radius: 3px; display: inline-block; }
  .project-photo img {
    width: 100%; max-width: 560px; border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: transform 0.4s ease;
  }
  .project-photo img:hover { transform: scale(1.02); }
  .caption { display: block; font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--light); margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .project-header { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.15rem; }
  }
</style>